metadata.name: The Maiden's Tower
metadata.description:
The Maiden's Tower, which was built on a small island in the Üsküdar district of Istanbul, off the coast of Salacak, is located on the Bosphorus.
Located at the point where two continents meet, in the middle of the Bosphorus, the Maiden's Tower has witnessed all periods from the Ancient Age to the Byzantine, from the Byzantine to the Ottoman with its 2500-year history.
As one of the most important symbols of Istanbul, the Maiden's Tower is an iconic address frequently visited by local and foreign tourists.
